    <item>
      <title>Do as I meant, not as I wrote</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/operatortypo/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 19:01:37 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/posts/operatortypo/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-worlds-worst-copy-assignment&#34;&gt;The world&amp;rsquo;s worst copy assignment&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I recently experienced a bug so nasty it made me reconsider my proclaimed &amp;ldquo;passion&amp;rdquo; for C++. Working on an implementation of a limit orderbook, I had implemented a &lt;code&gt;cancel&lt;/code&gt; method, simply removing an &lt;code&gt;Order&lt;/code&gt; object from a &lt;code&gt;std::vector&lt;/code&gt; using &lt;code&gt;erase&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-note-grid&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34;&gt;&#xA;        Note: This is a &amp;ldquo;Naive Vector&amp;rdquo; implementation for a future project comparing orderbook architectures - hence the obvious iterator invalidation!&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;note-column&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;span class=&#34;sidenote&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &#xA;        &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cpp&#34; data-lang=&#34;cpp&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;// ...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;it&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;_orders_by_id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;order_id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;];&lt;/span&gt; &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;orders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;erase&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;it&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt; &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;// ...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;But, the &lt;code&gt;Order&lt;/code&gt; was never removed. In fact, regardless of which &lt;code&gt;order_id&lt;/code&gt; I was attempting to remove, it would remove &lt;strong&gt;only&lt;/strong&gt; the last order. After stepping through the function in &lt;code&gt;gdb&lt;/code&gt; more times than I care to admit, I checked my implementation of the &lt;code&gt;Order&lt;/code&gt; class - and found this abomination.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
